hackathon-description-text: The Aston Computer Science Society is launching AstonHack, a student Hackathon to form part of the annual Major League Hacking (MLH) league.
hackathon-eligibility:
MLH events are free for student hackers aged 18+ participating in teams from 1 to 4 on innovative solutions to real-world problems.
. If you're not over 18 you cannot stay the night and will have to make arrangements to return to your usual accommodation.
hackathon-rules:
See 
Be respectful. Harassment and abuse are never tolerated. If you are in a situation that makes you uncomfortable at an officially sanctioned MLH event, if the event itself is creating an unsafe or inappropriate environment, or if interacting with a MLH representative or event organizer makes you uncomfortable, please report it using the procedures included in this document.
